til., <date TEIform=\"date\">ii/i B. C.</date>); a nom. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὑϊς</foreign> (scanned - <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">̆</itype>) <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ IG\">IG</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">12.472</biblScope> </bibl> (Boeotia, <date TEIform=\"date\">vi B. C.</date>), cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0261.tlg001:249\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Simon.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">249</biblScope> </bibl> (v. infr.); nom. pl. <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ὗες</quote_> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ IG\">IG</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">22.3632.24</biblScope> </bibl> </cit> (hex., Eleusis, <date TEIform=\"date\">ii A. D.</date>). The initial syll. is both <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">υἱ</foreign>-and <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὑ</foreign>-in <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Att.\">Att.</a></gram> </gramGrp> Inscrr. down to <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">400</biblScope> </bibl> B.C. (e. g. <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ὑεῖς</quote_> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ IG\">IG</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">12.115.14</biblScope></bibl></cit>, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὑέ[σιν]</foreign> ib.<bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">54.14</biblScope></bibl>, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὑόν</foreign> <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">v.</abbr> supr.), afterwards <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὑ-,</foreign> but <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">υἱός